@Node "COPYRIGHT"	"AFR.guide/Copyright"


	   The program AFR is shareware.
	   AFR may be distributed in public domain series, shareware discs/CDs
	   and networks if the following limitations are kept:


	1. You are allowed to copy AFR as often as you want, and for
	   everyone you want to copy it, but it is forbidden to
	   decompress the LHA-archive and to copy the single files.
	   Please copy only the whole archive.
	   
   	2. Any commercial use, especially distribution within 
   	   commercial products, needs the written permission
   	   of the author.
   	   
	3. In case of distribution via CD-ROM or similar not re-writable
	   media, it is allowed to present the AFR-package decompressed.
	   For this purpose you also need to get the author“s 
	   written permission.
	   And besides, the author should be offered a free copy.  
	

	   Disclaimers
	   ÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆ
	   No guarantee can be given that your AMIGA does not bite
	   the dust while running AFR, nor that a starship lands on
	   your houses“ roof.
	   Therefore, the author is not responsible for any damage
	   (directly or indirectly) caused by AFR.

	   The author DOES NOT guarantee that AFR is bug-free, nor
	   that AFR works without making any mistakes.

	   Please report bugs you may find to the author,
	   they will be removed as far as possible.

	   You use AFR at YOUR OWN RISK.




	@{"   Registration   " Link "REGISTER"}
@EndNode
@Node "WAS_IST"		"AFR.guide/About AFR"


	   The  program  AFR  is  shareware.  The  whole  of  AFR  and
	   its  external  programs  are  written  in    Assembler.

	   **							    **
	   **   Tested on different Amiga's,              	    **
	   **						 	    **
	   **   A500 A600 A1000 A2000 A3000 A4000 and others	    **
	   **						 	    **
	   **   Runs using any videographicsdapter. 		    **
	   **						 	    **
	   **   Runs using any turboboard.			    **
	   **						 	    **


	   AFR was programmed in order to run on Kickstart/Workbench 2.0
	   (and better). AFR does not run on Kickstart 1.3 and earlier
	   AmigaOS. Kick 1.3 is too old.

	   AFR replaces all the file requesters you know on the Amiga.
	   It provides you with features you won“t find in any other
	   file requester.

	   @{b}Why ?@{ub}

	   Why another file requester, you maybe ask.
	   I have  to admit  that there  are already  several file
	   requesters, BUT there things i am not satisfied with at
	   those requesters. Requester no.1 always forgets the dir it
	   read at the previous request, requester no.2 jumps to the
	   mouse pointer, just because the programmer thought that this
	   behaviour is useful. I bought a VGA-monitor and a flickerfixer,
	   thats a very fine equipment. The Workbench now measures the
	   double of its former size without flickering, but those
	   bloody file requesters do not care about it,
	   and using a videoadapter it“s even more worse.

	   The most of the Amiga users is upgrading to more RAM,
	   hard disc drives and other media keeping more data than a
	   floppy disc drive, and video adapters and VGA-monitors are
	   also not that rare.
	   Thats why I asked myself, why is it not possible to fit
	   programs into my equipment ?
	   Most of todays programs are still locked in certain pre-edited,
	   not changeable preferences that makes working with them
	   unnecesssarily hard. AFR is my contribution to make work
	   on the Amiga more efficiently and comfortable.

	   AFR will patch these existing libraries, providing that you enter
	   their names in the tooltypes of the AFR-icon:

	   - 'asl.library'
	   - 'reqtools.library'
	   - 'req.library'
	   - 'arp.library' (old, but still in use)

	   AFR uses a very sophisticated mechanism to patch these libs.
	   Therefore, you should have “SetFunction-Manager“ installed,
	   which is now included within the AFR-package.
	   “SetFunction-Manager“ makes the EXEC-vector “SetFunction“
	   able to multitask and should be installed on every Amiga
	   using AmigaOS 2.x and better.
	   By the way, it is also a product made in  my software-forge.

	   AFR also fits as Commodities-object into your system.

	   It is possible to completely localize AFR.


	   @{b}KEYBOARD@{ub}

	   You can also control AFR completely via keyboard, you do not
	   need your mouse, if you want to (are you still able to let
	   your mouse rest ?  :-))) ).


	   @{b}FONT@{ub}

	   AFR is full font-sensitive, it adjusts itself to the actual
	   screens“ font.
	   AFR also works using Proportional-Fonts, thus causes AFR to
	   be slower.
	   It is possible to pre-define a font for all or just one 
	   program. (feature not accessable yet)
	   

	   @{b}PARENT@{ub}

	   Click on with LMB to get to the parent dir,
	   click on with RMB to shorten pathname until colon.
	   

	   @{b}CHANGE DRAWER@{ub}

	   Let suppose you read your boot-partitions main-drawer.
	   You click on a drawer with LMB, the drive starts running
	   and reads the drawer, but before it has finished reading
	   you click on another drawer, which will be read right away.
	   After finishing reading this second drawer, the first 
	   selected drawer will be read and buffered.
	   Reading drawers is done by a separate task only supposed
	   to do read drawers.
	   

	   @{b}FORBID@{ub}

	   In case of AFR not working correctly with some program,
	   you can edit the preferences (Tooltypes) and enter that
	   this special program should not be served by AFR.
	   Please report incompatibilities to me, you will then receive
	   the latest version of AFR, that (i hope so) works with your 
	   program.
	   
	   	
	   AFR is freely configurable.
	   AFR has a programmable Rexxport.
	   AFR gives you the supervision about all Dos requesters.
	   
	   AFR and its external programs are being under
	   relentless development.
	  
	   Suggestions to improve AFR made by AFR“s user are being and will
	   be integrated, if they are possible and useful.

	   This version of AFR is now shareware.
	   Of course, the future of AFR depends on the amount of 
	   registrations.
	   

	   @{b}LIBRARY@{ub}

	   Does anyone need an “afr.library“ ???? If so, do you have
	   certain wishes concerning it ? Please tell me.
	   

	   @{"   Registration   " Link "REGISTER"}
@EndNode
@Node "HISTORY"	"AFR.guide/History"


***	Version 0.9	25 March 1994	***
	-first version, distributed to some beta-testers
	
***	Version 1.0	1 April 1994	***
	-directorys are filtered by the pattern
	-the filename can also be entered within the DirGadget
		
***	Version 1.01	6 April 1994	***
	-Exchange can (de)activate it
	
***	Version 1.02	5 May 1994	***
	-added a patterngadget
	-added a horizontal slider for ListView
	-corrected slight bugs in the library-patchroutines
	
***	Version 1.03	12 May 1994	***
	-added Assign,  Volume  and  Buffer-Gadget
	 and the corresponding gadgets for MultiSelect 

***	Version 1.04	27 May 1994	***
	-the displayed images are now font-sensitive
	
***	Version 1.05	June 1994	***
	-internal changes

***	Version 1.06	8 June 1994	***
	-the deviceses“ images are freely selectable
	-special functions with images be dragable above the window;
	 none of these are currently active, except releasing
	 Assigns and Lates onto the trashcan
	-clicking on the text behind the image buffers the contents
	 of the drawer
	-clicking on the image of a line causes the drawer to be read
	 but not buffered
	-leaving the activated line on the side with pressed LMB
	 causes the image of this line to be dragged above the screen
	 Which function do you like to have executed here ?
	 @{b}Suggestions are welcome.@{ub}

***	Version 1.062	13 July 1994	***
	-Bug fixed asl.library 40.x Kick 3.1

***	Version 1.063	July 1994	***
	-improved mechanism to patch libraries
	-rewritten asl.library-patch

***	Version 1.064	July 1994	***
	-widened addressing-range of texts
	-removed Enforcer-Hits

***	Version 1.07	27 July 1994	***
	-removed bugs in list management
	 no more bloody GURUs :-)
	-changed Alertfunction, works now with EasyRequest
	-by starting AFR again, it can now be removed

***	Version 1.071	11 August 1994	***
	-problems with A3000 eliminated and again
	-edited asl.library-patch
  	-keyboard-control programmed by 50% but not active yet
	-released as first FRAS-version

***	Version 1.07-8	December 1994	***
	-finished keyboard-control, improved scrollroutines
	-programming of Rexxport-module
	-registration-mechanism included
	-install-program was written
	-new images have been added
	-problems with several devices have been removed (ParNet...)

***	Version 1.09x	Jan-Jul 1995	***
	-awaited the last betatester-test while optimising AFR a
	 little bit
	-started functions using dragable images
	-released as shareware
	-this guide had also to be written ...

***	Version 2.0	August 1995	***
	-the positions of the different lists are now variable
	-started local preferences for every single program
	-built in new commands into Rexxport
	-fixed problems with CyberGFX
	-fixed problems with SCSI-commands
	-registration-routines finally done
	-now written the registration-program
	-keyboard-control is now accessable
	-local preferences will now be saved


	19.09.95 - AFR-Reader - Enforcer-hit fixed.
	20.09.95 - PrintManager - TAG_ASL_WINDOW=NULL Enforcer-hit fixed.
	21.08.95 - AFR refused to run under Ami-FileSave, now fixed
	21.09.95 - RexxPort caused Enforcer-hits under AFS, fixed
		   Message written to the programmers
	22.09.95 - AFR_Install Enforcer-hits fixed

	 8.10.95 - Rexx.AFR fits in even faster
	         - Rexx.AFR did not find 'RX' sometimes
	         - Rexx.AFR PlayMenu() timeout fixed
	         - Rexx.AFR StartNotify() obeys now also 'inactiv'
	         - Rexx.AFR new command: GadgetText()
	         - HotKey-task came sometimes up with asl-requester
	         - AFR can now be started using WBStartup+
	         - edited SCSI-Routinen
	         - edited registrationroutines

***	Version 2.1	Januar 1996	***
	21.01.96 - AFR-Reader - Enforcer-hit fixed.
	         - AFR is now cheaper

	27.01.96 - edited TAG_ITEM-execution
	           no more Gurus caused by not recognized TagItems
	         - edited AFR_Debug
	         - SetFunction is now part of the AFR-package

***	Version 2.200	March 1996	***
	14.03.96 - AFR-Reader - error 'interlock too deep' fixed
		 - filename can be longer when delivered from TAG-array
		 - AFR-registration can now be shifted with NewMode
		   and similar
		 - improved 'RALT-HELP'-call
		 - released into FRAS  :-)

***	Version 2.221	April 1996	***
	xx.04.96 - automatic Busypointer und Request() for windows (Ced).
		 - listscrolling in 5 steps (speed).
		 - at more than 999 files display was wrong at Multiselect
		 - removed bug in listscroll (at more than 1024).
		 - 'rexxafr.library' removed out of Rexx.AFR

		 - AFR now creates an “afr.library“ (the program gets gradually
		   too big, so that “bsr“ is not enough)
		 - Rexx.AFR now uses an offset -30 from “afr.library“ as a dispatcher
		 - Prog1.AFR (hotkey) uses routines from “afr.library“
		 - Rexx.AFR uses routines from AFR (shorter now)
		 - filter-functions did not work in 2.200, now fixed
		 - integrated xx_IntuiMsgFunc & xx_HookFunc & xx_FilterFunc
		 - horizontal widening of lists is now possible
		 - AFR forgot the window-position at repeated use
		   of the requester“s structure on a new screen (Ced)



***	Version 2.222	April 1996	***
		 - fixed bug in filter-function

@EndNode
@Node "INSTALL"		"AFR.guide/Install"



	AFR“s installation program installs AFR on your boot-partition
	(or in a drawer you enter) correctly.

	@{b}NO@{ub} files will be overwritten which have nothing to do
	with AFR ! Installation and even updates will only take place
	in the drawer @{b}AFR/@{ub}, at which the already installed
	version will be checked.

	Just double-click the install-icon on the workbench.
	Every step of installation will be explained.


 By the way,
	AFR is able to display a different image for each device.

	You can edit the file @{b}AFR/progs/Device_Info.AFR@{ub}
	in a texteditor and enter your devices.

	The line syntax is,
	@{b}Devicename		Brush		UNIT@{ub}

 e.g.:  trackdisk.device	Disk.br		0

	UNIT  can  be left out, if the brush to display is the
	same for all units

	Possible names for brush can be looked up in this drawer,
	AFR/Brush_08

@EndNode
@Node "REGISTER"	"AFR.guide/Registration"

	The program AFR is shareware.

	You are allowed to use AFR in its @{u}unlimited version@{uu} for some
	period of time, but afterwards you should register or otherwise
	delete AFR completely.

	The AFR-package includes the program AFR_Registration,
	which has to be used to register. The program is self-explaining.

	After the use of the registration-program,
	all functions of AFR will be @{u}fully accessable@{uu} again.

	@{" Register for one Amiga     " Link "REG_1"}

	@{" Register for more than one Amiga " Link "REG_2"}

	@{b}It is impossible to register without sending the file
	'RegisterMail.AFR' to me !@{ub}

	@{" How the file 'RegisterMail.AFR' gets to the author " Link "ANSCHRIFT"}

	You will be registered as soon as possible.
	If you do not send me this file, you will have to delete AFR.
	You are then no more allowed to use AFR.


@EndNode
@Node "REG_1"		"AFR.guide/Register for one Amiga"

	How to create the file 'RegisterMail.AFR'
	for one Amiga.

	1.1. Start AFR“s registration-program.
	1.2. Enter all data needed.
	1.3. Use 'Ok' to leave the program.
	     If the data were already entered, you can only leave the
	     program with “Cancel“.


	Now the file “RegisterMail.AFR“ can be found in your Ram-disc
	and should also be in AFR“s path on your hard disc.
	This file has now to be send to me.

	All data saved in this file are encrypted, and as a consequence,
	they cannot be read by another person.

	See also:	@{" Author“s address " Link "ANSCHRIFT"}
			@{" How to install the KeyFile " Link "KEYINSTALL"}

@EndNode
@Node "REG_2"		"AFR.guide/Register for more than one Amiga"

	How to create the file 'RegisterMail.AFR'
	for more than one Amiga.

	1.0 On the first Amiga :
	  1.1. Start AFR“s registration-program.
	  1.2. Enter all data needed.
	  1.3. Use 'Ok' to leave the program.
	       If the data were already entered, you can only leave the
	       program with “Cancel“.
	  1.4. Copy the file 'RAM:RegisterMail.AFR' to a floppy disc.


	2.0 On the next Amiga :
	  2.1. Copy the previous Amigas“ file 'RegisterMail.AFR'
	       from the floppy disc to this Amigas“ Ram-disc.
	  2.2. Start AFR“s registration-program.
	  2.3. Enter all data needed.
	  2.4. Use 'Ok' to leave the program.
	       If the data were already entered, you can only leave the
	       program with “Cancel“.
	  2.5. Copy the file 'RAM:RegisterMail.AFR' back to floppy disc.
	       The file should now be a litte bigger than before.
	  2.6. Restart at step 2.0 to register for another Amiga.

	'RegisterMail.AFR' has now to be send to me.

	All data saved in this file are encrypted, and as a consequence,
	they cannot be read by another person.

	See also
	@{" Author“s address " Link "ANSCHRIFT"}

	@{" How to install the KeyFile " Link "KEYINSTALL"}

@EndNode
@Node "KEYINSTALL"	"AFR.guide/How to install the KeyFile"

	How to install the KeyFile you will get from me, and
	there is no difference between if you registered for one
	or more Amigas.

	Please copy “KeyFile.AFR“ to your Ram-disc and start the
	registration-program again.
	The correct KeyFile will be created in AFR“s path.
	When restarting AFR it should come up with a message
	saying that your registration has been recognized.

@EndNode
