@Node "TOOLTYPES"		"AFR.guide/Tooltypes"


	PATCHARP	(YES|NO)
	PATCHREQ	(YES|NO)
	PATCHREQT	(YES|NO)
	PATCHASL	(YES|NO)
	@{"PATCHEASYREQ" Link "EASYREQ"}	(YES|NO)   (not yet implemented)
			The corresponding library will be patched.

	CX_POPUP	(YES|NO)

	CX_POPKEY	(<keys>) Default is 'ralt help'

	NUMBUFFERS	Sets maximum number of buffers to be held in
	     		memory.

	BUFFER		Reads drawer as normal buffer.

	ROMBUFFER	This type of buffer will not be set free
	      		automatically.

	HIDEROMBUFFER	RomBuffers are available but not visible in
			list

	READLATER	Causes AFR not to read RomBuffer and Buffer
			immediately when starting up.

	LISTMODE	V|B|A (drawers “v“, buffers “b“, assigns “a“)
			Sets where to display which list in the requester.


	@{b}AFR-variables in AFR“s pictogram start with the sign '$'
	and end with ':'.@{ub}


	INFOMODE	$BYTES: $PROTECT: $DATE: $TIME: $COMMENT:
			Sets which information and in which order to
			display it in Listview.

	REXXPORT	(YES|NO)
			Start Rexxport.

	NUMLOCK		(YES|NO)
			Tooltype in AFR“s pictogram.
			Turns on keyboard-control via numberblock.
			See also @{" Keyboard-control " Link "TASTATUR"}

	STATUSLINE	(YES|NO)
			Turn on statusline.

	STATUSSTR	$DEVICE: $VOLUME: $SIZE: $FULL: $FREE:
			$DIRS: $FILES: $BYTES:

			'$\\N:' activates the start of a new line and
			can only be entered once a time.

			Other texts in STATUSSTR are displayed normal !!
			E.g.,
			I am the device $DEVICE: and my name is $VOLUME:
			The output would be:
			I am the device DH0: and my name is WB3.1

	DEFMEMTYPE	CHIP|FAST
			Thats interesting for videographicsadapter-users.
			Some adapters allow the use of the keyword FAST.
			AFR“s ListView will then no more be emulated in CHIP
			but in FASTram.
			If the ListView remains empty then your adapter“s
			emulation is not able to blitter from FASTram.
			If this happens, reboot immediately and set this back
			to CHIP.

	STARTUP		<Filename> if REXXPORT=YES only
			Enter a file to be executed after AFR is loaded, e.g.
			starting notifys oder similar things only possible
			when AFR is in RAM.
			<Filename> can be a script, Rexxscript or executable.
			Set the “S“-flag in your script.
			STARTUP may appear several times in the pictogram.
			(feature not accessable yet)

@EndNode
@Node "EASYREQ"		"AFR.guide/EasyReq module"


	Modulename : "AFR/Progs/EasyReq.AFR"

	This module can be activated with the tooltype “PatchEasyReq“
	in AFR“s pictogram, and it takes the full control over any
	DOS-requester and other libraries“ textrequesters to you.
	You are able to completely suppress requesters, or to suppress
	requesters of certain tasks. It“s even possible to serve a displayed
	requester automatically.

	THIS MODULE IS STILL UNDER DEVELOPMENT.

@EndNode
@Node "SPEZIAL"		"AFR.guide/External/Special"

	Modulename : "AFR/Progs/Prog1.AFR"

	This module can be called by the hotkey entered in AFR“s
	pictogram, 'CX_POPUP=ralt help'.

	When being in a shell and wanting to start a program, but not
	knowing where it is located exactly, you can call AFR & click
	“SELECT“; then the whole path including the program“s name will
	be entered into your shell.

 	You can also call it to install a new tool with ToolManager.
     	Define which text should be written in which gadget;
     	activate a gadget, then press 'RALT-HELP'.

	Using this shortcut, a requester can be displayed at any time
	on the front screen. EGS is not supported (yet).

@EndNode
@Node "BESONDER"	"AFR.guide/Special features"


	@{b}The opened requester“s surface contains features not being
	visible at a glance.@{ub}

      - @{b}Local preferences.@{ub}
	You can define a requester-setting for every single program.
	Clicking on the toolsgadget with RMB will display a list of
	programs that have been working with AFR since it is in RAM.
	With the Checkmark being activated, the setting for the
	actual program will be saved after every change.
	With the Checkmark turned off, the setting will be saved only
	once a time.
	Every new program started which opens the requester, gets
	the settings of AFR_Default. These can be opened with
	Exchange “Display visible“.

      - @{b}The 'OK'-gadget.@{ub}
	Clicking on the “OK“-gadget with RMB is the same like with
	LMB, but the next requester will automatically be cancelled
	without	opening (Term and its uploadlist).

      - @{b}Delete files.@{ub}
        Click on a file in left ListView, hold mousebutton pressed and
        drag it out sidewards above the trashcan-gadget and release
        mousebutton. You will be asked if you want to delete
        this file.

      - @{b}Remove assign.@{ub}
	Click on an entry in the assignlist, drag it above the trashcan
	and release mousebutton. The assign will be removed.

      - @{b}Cancel device @{ub}
	Click on an entry in the volumelist, drag it above the trashcan
	and release mousebutton. This device will then no more be
	mounted and cannot be called.

      - @{b}Delete buffer-entry.@{ub}
	Click on an entry in the volumelist, drag it above the trashcan
	and release mousebutton. The memory used for this buffered
	drawer will be released.

      - @{b}Mount assign .@{ub}
	Drag an icon out of any list into the ListView of the assigns,
	then the drawer will be assigned as a logic device with a name
	you have to enter.
	(feature not accessable yet)

@EndNode
@Node "REXXPORT"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport"

	Modulename : "AFR/Progs/Rexx.AFR"

	Rexx.AFR programming supported by Rainer Simke.

	Rexxportname = 'AFR'. Rexx.AFR is under constant development,
	look out for new versions being published.

	@{"                  Important                 " Link "WICHTIG"}

