@Node "WICHTIG"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/Important"

	In order to avoid collisions with Rexx.AFR“s functionnames,
	it is possible to enter the prefix “AFR“; you can also give
	them unmissunderstandable names with the function ALIAS().
	E.g.,

	task = FindTask('Workbench')

	will then be

	task = AFRFindTask('Workbench')


	Each of these commands sets Rexx“s RC-variable; when
	everything is ok then its value is 1; in case of error its
	value is 0.

	To activate AFR“s Rexxport you have set the tooltype
	“REXXPORT=YES“ in AFR“s pictogram.

	After that all commands known to Rexx.AFR can be reached from
	ARexx as a function, without having to address AFR“s port.

	e.g.  RX "Say ScreenList()".

	The Rexxport is also under control of the commands DisableAFR
	and EnableAFR, making AFR deactivated or active.
	When AFR is deactivated, then only “EnableAFR“ can used via
	the Rexxport; this re-activates AFR.

	See also: @{"  Alias           " Link "ALIAS"}   @{"  KeyWordCtrl     " Link "KEYWORDCTRL"}
@EndNode
@Node "HELP"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/Help"

	CALL Help(NodeName)

	<NodeName> represents every name defined in this guide.
	Or just call a command of AFR“s Rexxport with the argument
	“?“.
	In both cases AmigaGuide will be started and the corresponding
	node will be displayed in AFR.guide.

	Examples:

	CALL Help(ScreenList)

	CALL PlayMenu(?)
	CALL ClickGadget(?)

	Help in a shell:

	> Rx "Call Help(ScreenList)"

@EndNode
@Node "KEYWORDCTRL"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/KeyWordCtrl"


	This adjusts AFR“s Rexxport in order to recognize only
	commands sent directly to it, and recognize only commands
	that are carrying the prefix “AFR“ in the commandname.


	CALL KeyWordCtrl( 1 )	   /* Control on */


	CALL AFRKeyWordCtrl( 0 )	/* Control off */

	or

	Address 'AFR'
	KeyWordCtrl 0		   /* Control off */

@EndNode
@Node "GetDiskObject"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/GetDiskObject"

	obj = GetDiskObject('Name')

	The stated object“s pictogram will be loaded.

	See also	@{"  PutDiskObject   " Link "PutDiskObject"}
			@{"  FreeDiskObject  " Link "FreeDiskObject"}
@EndNode
@Node "PutDiskObject"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/PutDiskObject"

	ok = PutDiskObject(obj,'Name')

	A pictogram loaded with GetDiskObject() will be saved with
	the stated name. Workbench-display refreshes if pictogram
	is displayed in a window.

	See also	@{"  GetDiskObject   " Link "GetDiskObject"}
			@{"  FreeDiskObject  " Link "FreeDiskObject"}
@EndNode
@Node "FreeDiskObject"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/FreeDiskObject"

	CALL FreeDiskObject(obj)

	Free a pictogram provided by GetDiskObject().

	See also	@{"  GetDiskObject   " Link "GetDiskObject"}
@EndNode
@Node "DeleteDiskObject"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/DeleteDiskObject"

	ok = DeleteDiskObject('Name')

	Deletes the stated pictogram (“Name“). Workbench-display will be
	refreshed if pictogram is in a displayed window.

@EndNode
@Node "FindToolType"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/FindToolType"

	1. n = FindToolType(obj)

	   Returns number of available tooltypetexts.


	2. Tooltypestring = FindToolType(obj,n)

	   The complete text of line <n> will be returned.


	3. Value = FindToolType(obj,ToolType)

	   Searches for a tooltype-entry in an opened pictogram which
	   has to be opened before. The text after the tooltype will
	   be returned.

	See also	@{"  GetDiskObject   " Link "GetDiskObject"}
			@{"  FreeDiskObject  " Link "FreeDiskObject"}
@EndNode
@Node "MatchToolValue"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/MatchToolValue"

	ok = MatchToolValue(obj,Tooltype,Value)


	See also	@{"  GetDiskObject   " Link "GetDiskObject"}
			@{"  FreeDiskObject  " Link "FreeDiskObject"}
@EndNode
@Node "AddToolType"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/AddToolType"

	ok = AddTooltype(obj,Tooltypestring)

	A whole tooltypetext will be added to the opened pictogram.

	Use PutDiskObject() to write changes.

	See also	@{"  GetDiskObject   " Link "GetDiskObject"}
			@{"  PutDiskObject   " Link "PutDiskObject"}
			@{"  FreeDiskObject  " Link "FreeDiskObject"}
@EndNode
@Node "DeleteToolType"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/DeleteToolType"

	ok = DeleteToolType(obj,Tooltype)
	ok = DeleteToolType(obj,n)

	Searches for a tooltype-entry in the opened pictogram and
	deletes it completely.

	Use PutDiskObject() to write changes.

	See also	@{"  GetDiskObject   " Link "GetDiskObject"}
			@{"  PutDiskObject   " Link "PutDiskObject"}
			@{"  FreeDiskObject  " Link "FreeDiskObject"}
@EndNode
@Node "IconValue"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/IconValue"

	Value = IconValue(obj,key)

	Reads pictogram-setting.

	ok = IconValue(obj,key,Value)

	Changes pictogram-setting.

	Keys possible:
	CurrentX , CurrentY , StackSize , DefaultTool , Type


	e.g.

	stack = IconValue(obj,STACKSIZE)     /* read StackSize */

	ok = IconValue(obj,STACKSIZE,10000)  /* set StackSize */


	See also	@{"  GetDiskObject   " Link "GetDiskObject"}
			@{"  PutDiskObject   " Link "PutDiskObject"}
			@{"  FreeDiskObject  " Link "FreeDiskObject"}
@EndNode
@Node "STARTNOTIFY"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/StartNotify"

	ok = StartNotify('_supervise_me_','_start_me_')

	Starts a file or path-supervision.
	_supervise_me_ is the complete path that may includes the
	file to supervise.

	_start_me_ is the name of the program, scipt or rexxscript
	to be executed when the function sends a message.

	The calling program will not be stopped.

	The _start_me_argument will be checked on existentence.


	e.g.

	-  Execute batchfile .
	  The 's'-flag of the batchfile has to be set.
	ok = StartNotify('S:file','S:User-startup')

	- Execute ARexxscript.
	ok = StartNotify('S:file','Rexx:DoSomething.rexx')

	- Execute program.
	ok = StartNotify('S:file','Prefs:ScreenMode')

	- Hand over command to be executed together with filename.
	ok = StartNotify('S:file',';Copy S:file BackUP:')
                                    ^
                                    | This sign is important !

	- Execute ARexxfunction.
	ok = StartNotify('S:file','/**/AFRBeep()')
                                    ^^^^
                                    |||| These signs are important !

	See also	@{"  DoNotify        " Link "DONOTIFY"}
			@{"  EndNotify       " Link "ENDNOTIFY"}
			@{"  ListNotify      " Link "LISTNOTIFY"}
			@{"  FindNotify      " Link "FINDNOTIFY"}
@EndNode
@Node "ENDNOTIFY"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/EndNotify  "

	CALL EndNotify('_supervise_me_')

	Supervising started with StartNotify() will be ended.


	See also	@{"  DoNotify        " Link "DONOTIFY"}
			@{"  StartNotify     " Link "STARTNOTIFY"}
			@{"  ListNotify      " Link "LISTNOTIFY"}
			@{"  FindNotify      " Link "FINDNOTIFY"}
@EndNode
@Node "DONOTIFY"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/DoNotify  "

	ok = DoNotify('_supervise_me_')

	File or path-supervision will IMMEDIATELY be started.

	The calling program will be stopped until a message or
	breaking-signal is received.

	The argument is the complete path that may includes the file
	to be supervised.

	See also	@{"  StartNotify     " Link "STARTNOTIFY"}
			@{"  EndNotify       " Link "ENDNOTIFY"}
			@{"  ListNotify      " Link "LISTNOTIFY"}
			@{"  FindNotify      " Link "FINDNOTIFY"}
@EndNode
@Node "LISTNOTIFY"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ListNotify "

	List = ListNotify()

	Gives a list of all supervised file/paths.

	Format:

	_supervise_me_ --> _start_me_
	Path/file      --> program|script

	See also	@{"  StartNotify     " Link "STARTNOTIFY"}
			@{"  EndNotify       " Link "ENDNOTIFY"}
			@{"  DoNotify        " Link "DONOTIFY"}
			@{"  FindNotify      " Link "FINDNOTIFY"}
@EndNode
@Node "FINDNOTIFY"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/FindNotify "

	ok = FindNotify('_supervise_me_')

	find a supervised file/path in the list

	See also	@{"  StartNotify     " Link "STARTNOTIFY"}
			@{"  EndNotify       " Link "ENDNOTIFY"}
			@{"  DoNotify        " Link "DONOTIFY"}
			@{"  ListNotify      " Link "LISTNOTIFY"}
@EndNode
@Node "INSERTKEY"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/InsertKey  "


	CALL InsertKey( <Keyword> )

	CALL InsertKey('a')		/* 'a' will be send as InputEvent */

	CALL InsertKey('rcommand shift c')
	CALL InsertKey('numpad *')
	CALL InsertKey('enter')

	The 'Keyword' will be send to input.device like pressing
	a key-shortcut on keyboard.

	See also	@{"  InsertString    " Link "INSERTSTRING"}
@EndNode
@Node "INSERTSTRING"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/InsertString"

	CALL InsertString('Hello world')

	The text will be send to input.device like a keyboard-input.

	See also	@{"  InsertKey       " Link "INSERTKEY"}
@EndNode
@Node "FINDTASK"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/FindTask    "

	TaskAddress = FindTask('TaskName')

@EndNode
@Node "WAITFORTASK"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WaitForTask "


	ok = WaitForTask('Task',timeout)


	Task    : Name of Program
	Timeout : Ticks

@EndNode
@Node "WAITFORTASKEND"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WaitForTaskEnd "


	ok = WaitForTaskEnd('Task',timeout)


	Task    : Name of Program
	Timeout : Ticks

@EndNode
@Node "FINDPORT"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/FindPort    "


	PortAddress = FindPort('PortName')

@EndNode
@Node "WAITFORPORT"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WaitForPort "

	ok = WaitForPort('PortName',timeout)

	PortName : Name of Port
	Timeout  : Ticks

@EndNode
@Node "PORTTASKNAME"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/PortTaskName"

	TaskName = PortTaskName('Port')	/* ask for programname
					   of a MessagePort */

@EndNode
@Node "BEFLIST"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/BefList     "

	Outputs all functionsnames of Rexx.AFR into shell.

	This will probably not remain as a part of Rexx.AFR,
	only for beta-information.

@EndNode
@Node "FILEREQUEST"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/FileRequest"

	? NP
	Got any idea for this ?
@EndNode
@Node "FONTREQUEST"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/FontRequest"

	? NP
	Got any idea for this ?
@EndNode
@Node "EASYREQUEST"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/EasyRequest"


	Var = EasyRequest('Title','Body'<VarX( %s %ld etz)>,'Gad1|Gad2|%s|..Gad<n>',Var1,Var2,...,Var12)


	Var = EasyRequest('AFR Rexx','This is %s good','%s|Continue','very','More about this')


	 --------------------------------
	| AFR Rexx                       |
	|--------------------------------|
        |                                |
	|	'This is very good'      |
        |                                |
        |--------------------------------|
	|More about this |     | Continue|
	 --------------------------------

	The user gets this request.
@EndNode
@Node "LISTREQUEST"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ListRequest"

	?  NP
	Got any idea for this ?
@EndNode
@Node "GETSTRING"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/GetString"

	? NP
	Got any idea for this ?
@EndNode
@Node "WINDOWPOS"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WindowPos"


	WPos = WindowPos('Window')	/* ask for position */

	WPos == 'LeftEdge,TopEdge,Width,Height'

	or

	CALL WindowPos('Window',LeftEdge,TopEdge,Width,Height)

	or

	CALL WindowPos('Window',WPos)

@EndNode
@Node "ACTIVEWINDOW"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ActiveWindow"


	Window = ActiveWindow(opt)		/* ask for the active window */


	opt  n : (default) address of Window in HEX
             t : result is the titeltext of window

@EndNode
@Node "ACTIVATEWINDOW"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ActivateWindow"

	ok = ActivateWindow('Window')	/* activate a certain window */

@EndNode
@Node "MOUSETOWINDOW"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/MouseToWindow"


	ok = MouseToWindow('Window')	/* Move mouse to a certain
					   window. Screen and window
					   will be moved to front. */
@EndNode
@Node "WINDOWSCREEN"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WindowScreen   "


	Screen = WindowScreen('Window')	/* This window belongs to which
					   screen ? */

@EndNode
@Node "WINDOWTOFRONT"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WindowToFront  "


	ok = WindowToFront('Window')	/* Move window to front */

@EndNode
@Node "WINDOWTOBACK"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WindowToBack   "


	CALL WindowToBack('Window')	/* Move window to background */

@EndNode
@Node "WINDOWLIST"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WindowList"


	WList = WindowList()	/* Display list of all windows */

	WList == Titel_Fenster_1#Titel_Fenster_2#Titel_Fenster_3 etc.

@EndNode
@Node "WINDOWTASKNAME"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WindowTaskName "


	TaskName = WindowTaskName('Window')

	Which program belongs to this window ?

@EndNode
@Node "SCREENTITLE"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ScreenTitle   "


	Titel = ScreenTitle('Screen')

	Returns the text of the screen-title.

@EndNode
@Node "FRONTPUBSCREEN"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/FrontPubScreen"


	FrontPubScreen = FrontPubScreen()

	Returns the front PublicScreen.

@EndNode
@Node "SCREENLIST"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ScreenList "


    ---	SList = ScreenList()			 /* get screenlist */
	SList == Screen1#Screen2#Screen3	 /* the result */

	or

    ---	SList = ScreenList(,",")		 /* get screenlist */
	SList == Screen1,Screen2,Screen3	 /* the result */


    ---	CALL ScreenList(Screen1#Screen2#Screen3) /* set screenlist */

	or

	CALL ScreenList(SList)			 /* set screenlist */

	or

	CALL ScreenList(Screen1,Screen2,Screen3) /* set screenlist */

@EndNode
@Node "SCREENTOFRONT"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ScreenToFront "


	CALL ScreenToFront('Screen')

	Move screen to front.

@EndNode
@Node "SCREENTOBACK"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ScreenToBack  "


	CALL ScreenToBack('Screen')

	Move screen to back.

@EndNode
@Node "TOGGLESCREEN"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ToggleScreen  "


	CALL ToggleScreen('Screen')

	Front screens will be moved to back,
	back screens will be moved to front.

@EndNode
@Node "MOVESCREEN"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/MoveScreen    "


	CALL MoveScreen('Screen',DeltaX,DeltaY)

@EndNode
@Node "SCREENDATA"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ScreenData    "


	data = ScreenData('Screen')

	data == LeftEdge TopEdge Width Height Depth ScreenName

@EndNode
@Node "FINDSCREEN"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/FindScreen    "


	Address = FindScreen('Screen')

@EndNode
@Node "WAITFORSCREEN"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WaitForScreen "


	ok = WaitForScreen(ScreenName,timeout)

	ScreenName  : Name of Screen
	Timeout     : Ticks

@EndNode
@Node "ADDPART"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/AddPart     "

	Two paths will be merged according to DOS-conventions.

	full = AddPart('pad1','pad2')

	When the second argument contains a ':', it will
	be returned in full length.

@EndNode
@Node "PATHPART"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/PathPart    "

	Cuts last part of a path like changing to parent dir.

	string = PathPart('sys:AFR/AFR.guide') ,

	The string will then be 'sys:AFR/'.

	The returned name contains either a colon or “/“. This makes
	file-handling in Rexx easy.


	Filepad = Dir || File

@EndNode
@Node "FILEPART"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/FilePart    "

	Ask for filename of a complete path.

	string = FilePart('sys:AFR/AFR.guide') ,

	The string is then 'AFR.guide'.

@EndNode
@Node "EXTPART"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ExtPart     "

	Ask for extension of a filename.

	string = ExtPart('sys:AFR/AFR.guide') ,

	The string is then '.guide'.

@EndNode
@Node "DELEXTPART"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/DelExtPart  "

	Removes extension of a filename.

	string = DelExtPart('sys:AFR/AFR.guide') ,

	reduces to 'sys:AFR/AFR'.

@EndNode
@Node "MATCHPATTERN"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/MatchPattern"

	ok = MatchPattern('patt','string')

@EndNode
@Node "BASECONV"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/BaseConv"

	Converts numbers (BIN/HEX/DEZ) to other formats.
	(dez=decimal)

	dez = BaseConv('%1000011000',D)

	hex = BaseConv('255')		/*  Hex is default  */

	bin = BaseConv('$FFE1',B)

@EndNode
@Node "READFILE"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ReadFile"

	NP
	Reads a file.

	bool = ReadFile('Datei',stemvar)


@EndNode
@Node "READZ"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ReadZ"

	NP
	Reads a certain line of a file.

	string = ReadZ('Datei',num)


	lastline = ReadZ('Datei',-1)

@EndNode
@Node "SORT"			"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/Sort"

	NP
	Sorts a file increasingly/decreasingly.
	(DOS is too slow at this)
@EndNode
@Node "WARPFORMAT"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/WarpFormat"

	NP
	Formats text or file into columns.

@EndNode
@Node "QUIT"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/Quit"

	Address AFR
	Quit

	The command makes the Rexxport-module quit and releases its
	memory. This command can only be send to ADDRESS AFR.

@EndNode
@Node "KILL"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/Kill"


	Address AFR
	Kill

	Everything relating to AFR including AFR releases its memory.

@EndNode
@Node "ENABLE"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/Enable"


	ok = EnableAFR()

	This command enables all activities of AFR.

	See also	@{"   DisableAFR   " Link "DISABLE"}
@EndNode
@Node "DISABLE"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/Disable"


	ok = DisableAFR()

	All activities of AFR will be disabled.
	To re-activate, only 'EnableAFR' will be accepted.

	See also	@{"   EnableAFR    " Link "ENABLE"}
@EndNode
@Node "MOUSEX"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/MouseX"


	This command sets the mouse“s X-co-ordinate.

	ok = MouseX( 320 )

	The actual position will be returned if called without
	co-ordinates:

	Xpos = MouseX()

	See also	@{"About mouse co-ordinates" Link "MOUSESPEZ"}
@EndNode
@Node "MOUSEY"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/MouseY"


	Sets mouse“s Y-co-ordinates.

	ok = MouseY( 200 )

	The actual position will be returned if called without
	co-ordinates:

	Ypos = MouseY()

	See also	@{" About mouse co-ordinates " Link "MOUSESPEZ"}
@EndNode
@Node "MOUSEPOS"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/MousePos"


	Sets new co-ordinates to mouse, where x has to be entered
	first.

	ok = MousePos( 320 , 200 )

	The actual position will be returned if called without
	co-ordinates, x and y are divided by a gap (spacebar).

	Pos = MousePos()

	See also	@{" About mouse co-ordinates " Link "MOUSESPEZ"}
@EndNode
@Node "MOUSECLICK"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/MouseClick"


	Simulates a mouseclick.
	Without x/y, the click will be executed at the actual position.

	ok = MouseClick( x , y )

	See also	@{" About mouse co-ordinates " Link "MOUSESPEZ"}
@EndNode
@Node "CLICKMOVE"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ClickMove"


	A mouseclick will be done at a defined position,
	the mousebutton remains pressed, the mouse moves and
	is released at an other defined position.
	This can be used for automatic moving of pictograms
	on Workbench or moving windows.

	ok = ClickMove( x1 , y1 , x2 , y2 )

	or

	ok = ClickMove( x2 , y2 )

	Take actual position for x1/y1.

	See also	@{" About mouse co-ordinates " Link "MOUSESPEZ"}
@EndNode
@Node "DOUBLECLICK"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/DoubleClick"


	Simulates a double-click.

	ok = DoubleClick( x , y )

	Without x/y, the double-click will be performed at the
	actual position.

	See also	@{" About mouse co-ordinates " Link "MOUSESPEZ"}
@EndNode
@Node "MOUSESPEZ"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/About mouse co-ordinates"


	Relative addressing of mouse-positions starts with “+“ or “-“.
	Positions to remain unchanged must be entered as “x“.

	ok = MousePos( x , '+10' ) Sets mouse 10 pixels below actual position.
				   X-co-ordinate remains unchanged.

		The arithmetic signs have to be set in brackets,
		otherwise REXX tries to calcute with them.

	ok = MousePos( 10 , 10 )  Sets mouse to 10,10; left upper corner.

@EndNode
@Node "PLAYMENU"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/PlayMenu"


	This commands lets you select in a menu by a "ghosthand".
	Be sure that the correct window is active.

	ok = PlayMenu( ItemName )
		ItemName should be unmissunderstandable, to make sure
		that the correct entry will be found.

	ok = PlayMenu( Menu , ItemName )
		Selects Item in menu 'Menu'.

	ok = PlayMenu( Menu , ItemName , SubItemName )
		Selects SubItem of the item 'Item' in menu 'Menu'.

	ok = PlayMenu( Menu , 2 , SubItemName )
		The items can reached by a number if they contain graphics.

	Names and numbers can variously be used for all menu-entries,
	but names should have a definite label.
	Names may be shortened, for the Workbenchmenu
	“Information ...“ just “Info“ is enough.

@EndNode
@Node "DELAY"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/Delay"


	Wait 1/50 of a second = 1.

	CALL Delay( 50 )    Wait 1 second.

@EndNode
@Node "WAIT"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/Wait"


	Wait a number of seconds.

	CALL Wait( 1 )      Wait 1 second.

@EndNode
@Node "ALIAS"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/Alias"


	You do not like the Arexxfunctionnames ? You cannot memorize them ?
	You are thinking of better names ? Just do it, rename them.
	Spaces in names are NOT allowed.

	ok = Alias( <old_name> , <new_name> )

	ok = Alias( 'MousePos' , 'MausP' )

	Now “MausP“ sent via Rexxport will be recognized as MousePos.
	The old name will also be recognized.
	A functionname will be sought in the aliaslist, and if not found,
	it will be sought in the standardlist.

@EndNode
@Node "MOUSETOGADGET"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/MouseToGadget"


	This command sets the mouse above the gadget identified by a
	number or by its text. Gadgets without text can only be called
	by their number.

	ok = MouseToGadget( 5 )

	ok = MouseToGadget( Cancel )


	SystemGadgets can only be reached with the following strings,

		ok = MouseToGadget( Size )
		ok = MouseToGadget( Drag )
		ok = MouseToGadget( UpFront )
		ok = MouseToGadget( DownBack )
		ok = MouseToGadget( Close )

	See also	@{"  ClickGadget    " Link "CLICKGADGET"}

@EndNode
@Node "CLICKGADGET"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/ClickGadget"


	This command clicks with the mouse on the gadget identified
	by a number or by its text. Gadgets without text can only be called
	by their number.

	ok = ClickGadget( 5 )

	ok = ClickGadget( Cancel )

	SystemGadgets can only be reached with the following strings,
		ok = ClickGadget( Size )
		ok = ClickGadget( Drag )
		ok = ClickGadget( UpFront )
		ok = ClickGadget( DownBack )
		ok = ClickGadget( Close )

	See also	@{"  MouseToGadget  " Link "MOUSETOGADGET"}

@EndNode
@Node "GADGETTEXT"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/GADGETTEXT"


	text = GadgetText( number )

	text = GadgetText( number , <new text> )

	text = GadgetText( <old text> , <new text> )

	This command returns a gadget“s text.
	A stringgadget“s content will be changed when the second
	parameter is stated.

@EndNode

@Node "SETENV"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/SetEnv"


	This command sets an ENV-variable.

	ok = SetEnv( VarName , content )
@EndNode
@Node "GETENV"	"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/GetEnv"


	This command returns an ENV-variable“s content.

	Inhalt = GetEnv( VarName )
@EndNode
@Node "UNSETENV"		"AFR.guide/External/Rexxport/UnSetEnv    "

	Deletes an ENV-variable.

	CALL UnSetEnv( VarName )
@EndNode
@Node "TASTATUR"	"AFR.guide/Keyboard-control"

	 @{b}TAB@{ub}
	 This key toggles between the several lists and displays.
	 You can also use this key with SHIFT.

	 @{b}RETURN@{ub}
	 <RETURN> jumps to the text-input-line.
	 If the line was activated before, the request will be confirmed.

	 @{b}ENTER@{ub}
	 Use the numberblock“s enter-key to read the path marked
	 by the display-bar and the display-bar jumps into main-display.

	 @{b}CURSOR-keys when a list is activ.@{ub}
	 Use cursor-up and cursor-down to move display-bar in a list.
	 Combinate with SHIFT or CTRL.

	 @{b}Cursor-right,@{ub} when display-bar is on a drawer, reads it.
	 When being on an file-entry, it will be (un)selected.

	 @{b}Cursor-left@{ub} reads parent dir.

	 @{b}CURSOR-keys when input-line is active@{ub}
	 Cursor-left/right are only used to move left/right.

	 @{b}Cursor-up/down@{ub} to search for a previously entered
	 text in the corresponding list. In the text-array for the file-
	 entry the keys can be shifted. Hereby no file will be sought,
	 but a drawer“s name. In the text-array, a combination with
	 >ALT< will  start the search in the list from the bottom.

	 If the @{" tooltype " Link "TOOLTYPES"} 'NUMLOCK' has been activated
	 in AFR“s pictogram, the numberblock can be used to control AFR.

	 Home, End, PgUp, PgDn, +, -, Ins, Del and the arrow-keys will when
	 have a function.

	 Home, End, PgUp, PgDn and the arrow-keys correspond to cursor-moves
	 with >SHIFT< or >CTRL<.

	 @{b}+ and - @{ub} like >TAB<.

         Use >@{b}CTRL+INS@{ub}< to toggle the state of “NUMLOCK“.
         This can only be done when AFR-requestwindow is active.

	 @{b}Del@{ub}  like dragging pictogram above trashcan.

	 @{b}F1@{ub}
	 Get previously displayed list back.

	 @{b}F2@{ub}
	 The local buffer-list for this program will be displayed in
	 main-display. The displayed buffers are only really buffered
	 if they occur in the buffer-list, otherwise only the name is
	 known.

	 @{b}F3@{ub}
	 displays volume-list in main-display.

	  @{b}F4@{ub}
	 displays assign-list in main-display.

	 @{b}F5@{ub}
	 displays buffer-list in main-display.

	 @{b}F6@{ub}
	 activates main-display. The following key-inputs will be
	 executed in this list.

	 @{b}F7@{ub}
	 activates volume-list.

	 @{b}F8@{ub}
	 activates assign-list.

	 @{b}F9@{ub}
	 activates buffer-list

	 @{b}F10@{ub}
	 displays prefs-list in main-display.
@EndNode
@Node "PROB"	"AFR.guide/Problems with AFR"


	When AFR causes problems with certain programs, you can tell
	AFR not to serve these programs.
	Enter the program name into the file AFR:Progs/Forbid_Info.AFR,
	and this programs gets the original requester using the
	original library.

	The name of the program that should not be served can be taken
	from the list displayed by AFR when clicking on the toolgadget
	with RMB in an opened requester, if your machine has not crashed
	at this point.  :-((.

	When you observe conflicts with Rexxscipts of other programs,
	then take advance of Rexx.AFR“s rexxcommand @{"KeyWordCtrl" Link "KEYWORDCTRL"},
	which reduces the response of the rexxport.

	The AFR-package contains the program “AFR_Debug“. This is a
	small support-program to detect bugs.

	Start AFR_Debug and leave the requester that appears open.
	Now start the program that doesn“t work with AFR, call a
	requester with it and close the requester with “Cancel“.
	Quit AFR_Debug by closing its requester that was left open.

	Your Ram-disc contains now the file “Debug.AFR“, which also
	includes the programname you can enter in “Forbid_Info“.
	Please send the file 'Debug.AFR' to me.

	Please report other problems that occur to me.

	@{" Author“s address " Link "ANSCHRIFT"}

@EndNode
@Node "HACKER"	"AFR.guide/Patches & hackers"

	!!! WARNING !!!
	For those who like to edit or change AFR in any way.

	AFR contains several routines to check itself on changes.
	If you like to have something changed,
	then please tell ME. :))

	KEEP OUT YOUR FINGERS !! That“s not joke !!

@EndNode
